{
  "texts": [
    "FruitChains [43] provides upper bounds on selfish mining revenue but suffers from zero-risk slightly profitable deviations.",
    "Other proposals like Bobtail [12] and StrongChain [56] that modify PoW mechanisms, or the DAG-based Tailstorm [33], lack comprehensive analysis of general selfish mining strategies.",
    "Sarenche et al. [49] suggested changing the difficulty-adjustment mechanism to consider blocks that are not in the longest chain, but this does not address petty-compliant miners who will then be incentivized to ignore these blocks to negate the effect.",
    "Colordag [4] was theoretically proven to resist selfish mining when its latency is impractically high and there are no adverse conditions.",
    "In contrast to all these works, MAD-DAG mitigates selfish mining under adverse conditions and with practical latency."
  ]
}